## Auto-Evidence Pipeline (NEW)
Chargeback cases are automatically matched to PMS reservations and evidence is collected:
1. reservationMatcher.js - Multi-strategy matching (confirmation#, card+dates, name+dates, card-only, name-only, email)
2. autoclerkEmulator.js - 10 guests, 13 reservations, 7 evidence types (folio, registration_card, payment_receipt, guest_signature, id_scan, reservation, audit_trail)
3. fraudDetection.js - Rule-based confidence scoring (15 positive + 10 negative factors, base score 50)
4. autoEvidenceCollector.js - Pipeline orchestrator: Match → Collect → Score → Notify
- Thresholds: >=85% AUTO_SUBMIT, >=70% REVIEW_RECOMMENDED, >=50% GATHER_MORE_EVIDENCE, <50% UNLIKELY_TO_WIN
- CaseDetail.jsx has "Auto-Collect Evidence" button that triggers the full pipeline
- "Respond to Cases" button replaces old "New Case" (chargebacks are received, not created)
- Dashboard + Cases header buttons turn red with urgent count badge when urgent cases exist

## Key Patterns
- Demo mode: DEMO_MODE=true in .env skips DB/Redis, uses mock data
- ALL backend catch blocks have demo fallbacks - zero 500 errors in demo mode
- Prisma deferred proxy: database.js uses JS Proxy to lazy-load PrismaClient
- AutoClerk PMS emulator: 10 guests, 13 reservations, 7 evidence types
- Global search: OR-logic across name, email, confirmation#, room, card, loyalty, room type, booking source
- Color palette: omni (blue) and omni-gold (amber) in tailwind.config.cjs
- Use .cjs extension for tailwind config (not .js)
- ChatHelp AI assistant widget on all pages
- Analytics KPI cards are clickable (navigate to filtered cases)
- All integration pages (PMS, OTA, Dispute) have working: Sign In (portal links), Configure modal, Connect/Disconnect, View Logs, two-way sync badges
- Multi-PMS support: Reservations page has PMS switcher tabs, backend accepts ?pmsSource= parameter
- Multi-integration: All 66 integrations can be active simultaneously across multiple properties
- OTA page: "Connect All" button, active integrations strip showing all connected OTAs
- Dispute page: Connect/Disconnect toggle per company, "Connect All" button, active integrations summary
- PMS page: Multi-PMS banner showing all connected PMS systems
- Login response structure: { message, user, tokens: { accessToken, refreshToken }, isDemo }

## API Endpoints (50 verified)

### Auth
- POST /api/auth/login - JWT authentication (returns tokens.accessToken)
- POST /api/auth/register - User registration
- POST /api/auth/refresh - Refresh token rotation
- GET /api/auth/providers - Auth provider list
- GET /api/auth/sessions - Active sessions
- POST /api/auth/logout - Logout

### Cases
- GET /api/cases - List chargeback cases (pagination, filters)
- GET /api/cases/:id - Case detail (includes auto-collected evidence)
- POST /api/cases/:id/submit - Submit case response to processor
- POST /api/cases/:id/notes - Add case note
- POST /api/cases/:id/arbitration - File arbitration for lost case
- POST /api/cases/:id/auto-collect - Auto-collect evidence pipeline (match→collect→score)
- GET /api/cases/:id/documents - Uploaded supporting documents

### Evidence
- GET /api/evidence - All evidence across cases
- GET /api/evidence/:caseId - Evidence for specific case
- POST /api/evidence/:caseId/collect - Collect from PMS (returns analysis)
- POST /api/evidence/:caseId/upload - Manual evidence upload
- GET /api/evidence/:caseId/summary - Evidence completeness summary

### Analytics
- GET /api/analytics/dashboard - Dashboard KPIs
- GET /api/analytics/trends - Trend data

### PMS
- GET /api/pms/connected - Connected PMS systems
- POST /api/pms/connect - Connect a PMS
- POST /api/pms/sync - Trigger PMS sync
- PUT /api/pms/config - Configure PMS settings
- POST /api/pms/disconnect - Disconnect PMS

### Reservations
- GET /api/reservations/pms/status - PMS connection status
- GET /api/reservations - List reservations (?pmsSource= for multi-PMS)
- GET /api/reservations/:id - Reservation detail
- GET /api/reservations/:id/evidence - Evidence for reservation

### Other
- GET /api/disputes/companies - 27 dispute processor companies
- GET /api/notifications/unread-count - Notification count
- GET /api/admin/users - User management
- GET /api/admin/properties - Property management
- GET /api/admin/agents - AI agent list (4 agents)
- PUT /api/admin/settings/* - Settings (general, notifications, ai-defense, integrations, password)
- GET /api/sync/status - Sync status

## Conventions
- All routes return JSON with consistent error format
- Frontend uses Lucide React icons exclusively
- Tailwind utility classes, no CSS modules
- React functional components with hooks only
- JWT tokens stored in localStorage via useAuth context
- Node 20 LTS required (Node 25 has severe CJS performance issues)
- Backend startup loads 66 integrations
- Chargebacks are RECEIVED from processors, not created by users — no "New Case" UI

